00:15:53,245 --> 00:15:57,416
You know, Ray,
your contract with Atlantic
is expiring in four months.

376
00:15:57,708 --> 00:15:58,750
Yeah.

377
00:15:58,876 --> 00:16:00,752
Yeah, I've got
the contract with me.

378
00:16:00,878 --> 00:16:02,880
They're going to
double my royalties.

379
00:16:02,880 --> 00:16:04,882
Before we jump back
in that pond,

380
00:16:05,007 --> 00:16:07,176
I thought I'd find out
what else was out there.

381
00:16:07,259 --> 00:16:10,888
I had a very productive chat
with ABC-Paramount yesterday.

382
00:16:11,013 --> 00:16:12,890
ABC? Who told you
to do that, huh?

383
00:16:13,015 --> 00:16:16,018
And you know,
Atlantic is family,
just like the Shaw Agency.

384
00:16:16,059 --> 00:16:18,478
Ray, my job is to get you
the best deal possible.

385
00:16:19,188 --> 00:16:21,148
ABC is very interested.

386
00:16:21,190 --> 00:16:22,191
No.

387
00:16:24,902 --> 00:16:26,195
How interested?

388
00:16:27,070 --> 00:16:31,992
How about
a $50,000 advance
each year for three years?

389
00:16:32,034 --> 00:16:34,161
You produce
your own records.

390
00:16:34,495 --> 00:16:37,039
They'll deduct recording costs
and give you

391
00:16:37,456 --> 00:16:39,041
75 percent.

392
